// useDesignTextEdit
// Manages an invisible textarea overlay for text input when a text node is being edited in the design canvas.

An off-screen textarea (opacity:0, 1x1px) receives keyboard and IME input so the OS input stack works normally.
A blinking caret is simulated by toggling caretVisible at 530ms intervals.
The hook is active only while editingTextId is set in the editor store.

FUNCTION useDesignTextEdit(canvasRef)                                           EXPORT
  CALLS: useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore), getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs),
         adjustRunsForDelete (style-runs), adjustRunsForInsert (style-runs),
         toggleBoldInRange (style-runs), toggleItalicInRange (style-runs), toggleDecorationInRange (style-runs)
  When editingTextId becomes non-null: creates and appends a hidden textarea, focuses it, starts the caret blink timer,
  and registers all text input event handlers.
  When editingTextId becomes null: removes the textarea, stops the blink timer, and clears all handlers.

---

FUNCTION getEditingNode() -> SceneNode | null
  Reads the current editingTextId from the store and returns the corresponding node from the scene graph.

---

FUNCTION resetBlink()
  Resets caretVisible to true, clears the existing blink interval, and starts a new one that toggles
  caretVisible every 530ms and requests a repaint.

---

FUNCTION syncText(nodeId, text, runs?)
  Updates the node's text (and optionally its styleRuns) in the scene graph, then requests a render.

---

FUNCTION insertText(text, node)
  Adjusts styleRuns for any deleted selection range and then for the inserted text length.
  Delegates the actual cursor/text state update to the textEditor, then syncs to the scene graph.

---

FUNCTION deleteText(node, forward)
  Adjusts styleRuns for the deleted character(s) or selection range.
  Delegates backspace/delete to the textEditor, then syncs to the scene graph.

---

FUNCTION applyFormatting(nodeId, changes, label)
  Applies a style change (bold, italic, underline) as an undoable action, rebuilds the paragraph
  in the textEditor, and requests a render.

---

FUNCTION onCompositionStart()
  Sets isComposing to true so onInput events are suppressed during IME composition.

---

FUNCTION onCompositionEnd(e)
  Clears isComposing, inserts the composed text, empties the textarea value, and resets the caret blink.

---

FUNCTION onInput()
  Skipped if currently composing. Reads the textarea value, clears it, and inserts the text into the node.
  Resets the caret blink.

---

FUNCTION onKeyDown(e)
  Handles all keyboard interactions during text editing:
  Escape: commits the text edit and returns focus to the canvas.
  Enter: inserts a newline.
  Backspace/Delete: deletes the selection or a single character; Cmd/Alt modifiers extend the deletion range.
  Arrow keys: moves the cursor (or extends selection with Shift); Cmd/Alt modify movement distance.
  Cmd+A: select all. Cmd+C: copy selection to clipboard. Cmd+X: cut selection to clipboard.
  Cmd+V: paste from clipboard and insert.
  Cmd+B: toggle bold on selection or whole node. Cmd+I: toggle italic. Cmd+U: toggle underline.

---

FUNCTION onCanvasMouseDown()
  When the canvas is clicked during text editing, re-focuses the hidden textarea on the next frame
  so keyboard input is not lost.
